<MELItem itemNbr="50-20-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-50-20-01.1.2-50-20-01">
<Title>Cargo Handling Systems</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="D" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="0">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative or portions of the system may be missing.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>Any portion of the system which operates normally may be used.</Para>
</Note>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceNote>
<Para>Manual operation features of the cargo handling system allow loading and unloading of ULDs when electrical components are inoperative.</Para>
<Para>Open holes in the ball mats where Power Drive Units (PDUs) have been removed should be covered to avoid injury to cargo handlers. For structural damage to the ball mats (e.g., cracks, nicks, scratches, gouges, corrosion, dents, holes and punctures), refer to the Structural Repair Manual (SRM).</Para>
</MaintenanceNote>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
